Des Rapides Park is an urban park in Montreal, Quebec, Canada. Located adjacent to the Lachine Rapids in the borough of LaSalle, Des Rapides Park is part of the City of Montreal's Network of Large Parks. The park is 30 hectares large. It has been a migratory bird sanctuary since 1937, and is home to over 225 species of bird, among these is the great blue heron, a protected species.

In the LaSalle district of Montreal, the special terrain of Rapids Park on the St. Lawrence River has formed a turbulent rapids island. This is undoubtedly a gift from heaven, making the people living around here feel like a paradise. This whitewater island, also known as Aviary Island, is located at the southeastern tip of Montreal Island, facing Sister Island. Covering an area of ‚Äã‚Äã30 acres, the park has been one of the most beautiful migratory bird sanctuary in Canada since 1937. Every year, 225 species of birds come here to inhabit, among which the blue heron is a rare protected animal.
